sequenceDiagram
    participant U as User / Browser
    participant C as Client App
    participant AS as Authorization Server
    participant DB as PostgreSQL

    C->>C: Generate code_verifier
    C->>C: Derive code_challenge = BASE64URL(SHA256(code_verifier))
    C->>AS: GET /oauth2/authorize<br/>client_id, redirect_uri, response_type=code,<br/>scope, state, code_challenge, code_challenge_method=S256
    AS->>DB: Validate client and exact redirect_uri match
    AS->>DB: Store auth_code + code_challenge + subject + scope + 5 min expiry
    AS-->>U: 302 redirect to redirect_uri?code=AUTH_CODE&state=STATE
    U->>C: Browser returns with authorization code
    C->>AS: POST /oauth2/token<br/>grant_type=authorization_code,<br/>code, client_id, code_verifier
    AS->>DB: Load unused auth_code and verify client_id
    AS->>AS: Recompute SHA256(code_verifier) and compare to stored code_challenge
    AS->>DB: Mark auth_code consumed
    AS->>DB: Issue access_token + refresh_token
    AS-->>C: 200 OK with tokens
    C->>AS: GET /api/resource with Bearer access_token
    AS->>DB: Validate token exists, active, unexpired
    AS-->>C: Protected resource response
